From c06e07cc3175338fe681d6707983eae6a6b9e5af Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Bohdan Chubuk <chbgdn@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 07:54:44 +0300
Subject: [PATCH 12/12] netfilter: nft_flow_offload: Set hw_ifidx in
 nft_dev_fill_bridge_path()

Without this, the flow_offload_tuple out.hw_ifidx remains 0 when a
bridge flow is offloaded. The PPE (hardware offload engine) on airoha
and similar SoCs uses hw_ifidx to determine the egress port. When it
is 0, the PPE binds the flow entry but cannot forward any packets.

Fixes the bridge HW offload path which was missing the hw_ifidx
assignment present in the routed offload path (nft_dev_forward_path
sets route->tuple[dir].out.hw_ifindex = info.hw_outdev->ifindex, which
is later copied to hw_ifidx by flow_offload_route_init).
---
 net/netfilter/nft_flow_offload.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/net/netfilter/nft_flow_offload.c b/net/netfilter/nft_flow_offload.c
index 926b88c36372..5fc5e0e34179 100644
--- a/net/netfilter/nft_flow_offload.c
+++ b/net/netfilter/nft_flow_offload.c
@@ -354,6 +354,7 @@ static int nft_dev_fill_bridge_path(struct flow_offload *flow,
 	ether_addr_copy(th[dir].tuple.out.h_source, src_ha);
 	ether_addr_copy(th[dir].tuple.out.h_dest, dst_ha);
 	th[dir].tuple.out.ifidx = info.outdev->ifindex;
+	th[dir].tuple.out.hw_ifidx = info.hw_outdev->ifindex;
 	th[dir].tuple.xmit_type = FLOW_OFFLOAD_XMIT_DIRECT;
 
 	return 0;
